---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const schema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'AboutPage',
  mainEntity: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: 'Ivan Stamenov',
    jobTitle: 'Founder, RecastCalc',
    description: '25+ year marketing and finance executive with experience at McKinsey, Merkle/Dentsu, and PE-backed multi-site service platforms.',
    url: 'https://recastcalc.com/about/',
  },
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About RecastCalc — Independent Mortgage Calculators"
  description="RecastCalc is an independent mortgage utility site built by Ivan Stamenov, a 25-year marketing and finance executive with McKinsey, Merkle/Dentsu, and PE-backed services experience."
  schema={schema}
>
  <article class="max-w-prose mx-auto px-4 lg:px-6 py-16 prose-recast">
    <h1 class="text-display-1 font-display font-semibold mb-8">About RecastCalc</h1>

    <h2>What this site is</h2>
    <p>
      RecastCalc is a focused set of mortgage utility calculators built to be more useful and more
      honest than what's currently available online. Every calculator shows competing strategies
      side-by-side — including the ones that don't generate revenue for us — so that the user can
      make a decision based on math, not on whichever option pays the highest referral fee.
    </p>

    <h2>Who built it</h2>
    <p>
      I'm <strong>Ivan Stamenov</strong>. I have 25+ years of operating experience across marketing,
      finance, and private-equity-backed services. My career includes McKinsey & Company, Merkle/Dentsu,
      Cancer Treatment Centers of America, and operating partner roles at Varsity Healthcare Partners
      and several PE-backed multi-site platforms in healthcare services.
    </p>
    <p>
      I built RecastCalc because I needed the recast calculator myself, found that none of the
      existing ones showed the comparison I wanted, and realized that gap exists across most
      mortgage tools online. The economics of the project — independent operator, ad-supported,
      no lender ownership — make it possible to publish the comparisons that lender-owned tools
      structurally avoid.
    </p>

    <h2>What we are not</h2>
    <p>
      RecastCalc is <strong>not</strong> a lender, a mortgage broker, a financial advisor, or a
      licensed real estate professional. We do not originate loans, we do not give personalized
      financial advice, and we do not endorse any specific product. The calculators are estimates
      based on standard amortization formulas; consult a licensed mortgage professional or
      Certified Financial Planner before making decisions involving real money.
    </p>

    <h2>How we make money</h2>
    <p>
      Two sources, both clearly disclosed:
    </p>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
      <li><strong>Display advertising</strong> via Google AdSense. Ads are placed below calculator results, never above. We never sell ad placement, never accept "sponsored content," and never modify calculator math based on advertiser interests.</li>
      <li><strong>Affiliate commissions</strong> from optional links to lender comparison platforms (LendingTree, Credible). These are clearly labeled "Sponsored" and use <code>rel="sponsored nofollow"</code>. Commissions do not change what we recommend or how the calculators behave.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      We do not collect email addresses, do not gate calculators behind signups, and do not sell
      data. See our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Editorial integrity</h2>
    <p>
      Every calculator on this site is reviewed against published amortization standards and
      stress-tested against scenarios from CFPB consumer guides, Freddie Mac documentation, and
      lender disclosures. When we recommend a strategy, we show the math. When the math says the
      strategy that costs us money is the better choice for the user, we say so.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions, corrections, or partnership inquiries: see our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
